Overview

This Marketing programme at City University of Hong Kong is designed to nurture marketing professionals and entrepreneurs. After completing this programme, students should be able to:
?acquire advanced knowledge of marketing philosophy, principles and techniques;
?develop critical awareness of contemporary strategic marketing issues from international perspectives;
?apply analytical tools including state-of-the-art software commonly used in marketing to respond operationally in dynamic, complex marketing environments and to make sound marketing decisions;
?develop a keen social conscience, through application of high ethical standards in the field of marketing.

Career Prospects

As a major commercial centre in Asia, Hong Kong has provided rich opportunities for graduates equipped with advanced marketing knowledge and techniques. 

The ambitious graduates will be equipped to work for a wide range of organizations both in Hong Kong and internationally, in a variety of areas such as marketing management, advertising, marketing research, business consultancy and sales management. Graduates may also pursue PhD studies.
